com.illposed.osc.utility

Class OSCByteArrayToJavaConverter

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.illposed.osc.utility.OSCByteArrayToJavaConverter

  • public class OSCByteArrayToJavaConverter
extends java.lang.Object
    Utility class to convert a byte array, conforming to the OSC byte stream format, into Java objects.

      • convert

        public OSCPacket convert(byte[] bytes,
                int bytesLength)
        Converts a byte array into an OSCPacket (either an OSCMessage or OSCBundle).
        Parameters:
        bytes - the storage containing the raw OSC packet
        bytesLength - indicates how many bytes the package consists of (<= bytes.length)
        Returns:
        the successfully parsed OSC packet; in case of a problem, a RuntimeException is thrown

      • isBundle

        private boolean isBundle(OSCByteArrayToJavaConverter.Input rawInput)
        Checks whether my byte array is a bundle. From the OSC 1.0 specifications: The contents of an OSC packet must be either an OSC Message or an OSC Bundle. The first byte of the packet's contents unambiguously distinguishes between these two alternatives.
        Returns:
        true if it the byte array is a bundle, false o.w.

        private java.lang.Long readUnsignedInteger(OSCByteArrayToJavaConverter.Input rawInput)

      • readTimeTag

        private java.util.Date readTimeTag(OSCByteArrayToJavaConverter.Input rawInput)
        Reads the time tag and convert it to a Java Date object. A timestamp is a 64 bit number representing the time in NTP format. The first 32 bits are seconds since 1900, the second 32 bits are fractions of a second.
        Returns:
        a Date
